Coloration (in preservative). Body dorsum grayish brown with a series of weakly developed darker brown crossbars, one across occiput and nape, one across shoulders, two between axilla and groin, and one on anterior part of sacral region, another bar on tail base. A faint pale vertebral line bisecting anterior 3 crossbars. Flanks with some faint mottling. Limbs mottled. Tail with faint alternating brown and white bands, becoming bolder at approximately one third of tail length from cloaca, faint again on distal portion of tail. Head medium brown with beige labial scales, rictus, and posteroventral orbital margin. Venter cream, palms and soles grayish. Coloration in life (
Fig. 3
) generally similar to that in preservative, but darker and more contrasting. The iris was amber in colour.
